bruary 2026\n- It's an experimental, lightweight AI programming assistant that runs directly in the terminal\n- Two operating modes:\n  - **Suggestion mode** (default): Proposes commands for user confirmation\n  - **Fully automatic mode**: Operates autonomously with safety constraints (network disabled, sandboxed directories)\n- Features: Zero configuration, multi-modal capabilities (can process screenshots/sketches), supports o3 and o4-mini models\n- Fully open-sourced on GitHub\n\n### Other Notable Command-Line AI Tools\n- **Claude Code by Anthropic** - Launched February 24, 2025\n- **Gemini CLI by Google** - Released June 25, 2025, open-sourced with Apache 2.0 license\n- **Cline** - Open-source alternative to Cursor, available as a VS Code extension\n\n### February 2026 Context\nThe search mentions OpenAI's new MacOS app for agentic coding launched in **February 2026**, which builds upon their existing Codex command-line tool from April 2025.\n\n**Note**: The search results don't show a specific NEW command-line AI coding tool launched in February 2026 itself. Rather, February 2026 appears to be when OpenAI launched a MacOS app that integrates with their existing command-line coding tools (Codex CLI from April 2025).\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
