port, works with 75+ LLM providers\n   - Installation available via npm, brew, and other package managers\n\n2. **Claude Code**\n   - Advanced reasoning capabilities directly in the terminal\n   - Can explore repositories, edit files, run shell commands, and commit changes\n   - Pay-per-use pricing based on token consumption\n\n3. **Gemini CLI**\n   - Offers million-level native context for understanding entire projects\n   - Can handle entire codebase, dependency trees, and commit history\n\n4. **Codex CLI**\n   - Direct terminal access to OpenAI's coding models\n   - Uses the o4-mini model optimized for software engineering\n   - Lightweight, focused on fast interactions\n\n5. **Aider**\n   - AI pair programming tool for the terminal\n\n### Industry Trends (2026):\n\n- **Shift from \"completion plugins\" to \"agentic execution\"** - AI tools are moving from simple autocomplete to autonomous agents that can fix errors, run tests, and verify results\n- **Terminal-first approach** - These agents live entirely in the command line, integrating with Git and project structures\n- **Multi-file refactoring** - Capable of handling complex tasks spanning dozens of files\n\n**Note:** The search results show articles from late 2025 and January 2026 discussing these tools, but I didn't find a specific product launch announced exactly in February 2026. It's possible that either:\n- The launch date you're looking for hasn't been widely indexed yet\n- The specific tool or date might be from a different source not captured in this search\n\nWould you like me to search for a more specific product name or company?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
