ry-Wide AI Response (February 2026)**\nGitHub's move triggered a competitive response from other platforms:\n- **OpenAI** (early February 2026): Released Copilot Pro upgrade with AI-driven code security scanning\n- **GitLab** (late January 2026): Launched AI-powered Merge Request Automation for automatic code conflict resolution\n- **Bitbucket**: Partnered with Anthropic to offer tools based on Claude 3, focusing on open-source security vulnerability fixes\n\n### 3. **GPT-Migrate Tool**\nA dedicated AI code migration tool called **GPT-Migrate** is available:\n- Helps migrate codebases from one framework or language to another\n- Available on GitCode: https://gitcode.com/gh_mirrors/gp/gpt-migrate\n- Designed to automate cross-platform code migrations\n\n### 4. **Claude Code (February 2026)**\nAnthropic's Claude Code continues to be mentioned as an \"agentic\" AI coding tool, with ongoing developments through February 2026.\n\n### 5. **GitHub Copilot Model Updates**\nGitHub documentation mentions that complimentary access to Grok Code Fast 1 ended on February 17, 2026, indicating ongoing model updates and changes.\n\nThe search results show an intense \"AI arms race\" in the code hosting and development tools space, with major platforms competing to offer the most advanced AI-powered automation and migration capabilities in early 2026.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
