ls that were launched exactly in February 2026. Here's what I found:\n\n## AI Programming Tools (February 2026 Context)\n\n### Featured Tools from Recent Coverage:\n\n**1. JetBrains AI Assistant** (Featured in February 2026 reviews)\n- **Refactoring & Debugging**: Batch refactoring while preserving business logic\n- **Debugging Capabilities**: Natural language interaction during breakpoints to analyze stack traces and provide fix suggestions\n- **Test Generation**: Automatic unit test generation support\n- **Language Support**: Multi-language support though primarily optimized for Java and Python developers\n- **Git Integration**: Automatic summarization of code change history\n\n**2. Claude Code**\n- Demonstrated capability in migrating React Testing Library from v13 to v14 (970 test files, 6000+ test cases)\n- Strong performance in debugging and test fixing\n- Can generate migration guides and codemods\n\n**3. Refact.ai**\n- **Unit Test Generation**: Automated test case creation\n- **Code Refactoring**: Complex code conversion capabilities\n- **Debugging**: Error detection and fixing assistance\n- **Features**: Self-hosting option, BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) functionality\n\n**4. Replit AI**\n- Cloud-based integrated development platform\n- Real-time code completion (Ghostwriter)\n- Natural language to full-stack application conversion\n- Supports 20+ programming languages\n\n### Other AI Tools Mentioned:\n\n**5. Sourcery**\n- Code quality optimization specialist\n\n**6. TENET (Purdue University)**\n- Interactive debugging tool allowing line-by-line code execution\n- AI-driven test-driven development implementation\n\n**7. Atlassian Rovo Dev**\n- Code analysis, generation, and debugging assistance\n- Test generation capabilities\n\nThe search results primarily show comprehensive reviews and comparisons of existing AI programming tools rather than new product launches specifically in February 2026. The tools featured represent the current state of AI-assisted development, with capabilities spanning debugging, refactoring, and test generation.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
