i-step tasks including writing code and debugging\n- Compatible with IntelliJ IDEA Ultimate, PyCharm Pro, WebStorm, and GoLand\n- Support coming soon for PhpStorm, RustRover, and RubyMine\n\n## Cross-Platform AI Solutions\n\n### JetBrains AI Assistant for VS Code\n- JetBrains released **AI Assistant for Visual Studio Code** as a public preview\n- Features include:\n  - Code completion powered by GPT-4o\n  - Code explanation and documentation generation\n  - Multi-file editing capabilities\n  - Context-aware code understanding\n  - Integration with coding agents for complex tasks\n\n### RunVSAgent Plugin\n- An innovative tool that allows developers to **run VSCode-based coding agents within JetBrains IDEs**\n- Supports popular VSCode AI agents like Roo Code, Cline, and Kilo Code\n- Compatible with the entire JetBrains IDE family (IntelliJ, PyCharm, WebStorm, etc.)\n- Provides a unified agent experience across different IDE platforms\n\n## Key Trends\n1. **Convergence**: AI tools are becoming available across both VS Code and JetBrains platforms\n2. **Free tiers**: Major players are offering free AI coding capabilities to compete\n3. **Coding agents**: Shift from simple code completion to autonomous agents that can handle multi-step tasks\n4. **Local AI options**: Growing support for offline/local AI model execution for privacy-conscious developers\n\nThe search results show that as of February 2026, there's significant competition and innovation in the AI coding space, with both VS Code extensions and JetBrains plugins offering increasingly sophisticated capabilities.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
