D (Document-Driven AI Development)**: Emerging paradigm for 2026\n- **Agentic Coding**: Evolution from code completion to autonomous agent programming\n\n### Notable Tools Mentioned:\n- **Cherry Studio**: 39.1k stars - AI Agent + Coding Agent with 300+ assistants\n- **Agent S**: Open agentic framework with local coding environment support\n- **ChatAgent**: Local deployment tool for general-purpose AI agents\n- **Self-Hosted AI Starter Kit**: Open-source template for quick local AI environment setup by n8n\n\n## 💡 Key Features of 2026 Local AI Coding Agents:\n\n1. **Security**: Local execution, self-hosted models, data stays on-device\n2. **Privacy**: No cloud API requirements\n3. **Autonomy**: Agents can independently break down requirements, write code, and test\n4. **Integration**: Support for multiple platforms and LLM providers\n5. **Ease of Use**: GUI interfaces, one-click deployment, beginner-friendly\n\nThe landscape shows a clear trend toward decentralized, privacy-focused AI coding agents that can run locally without depending on cloud services, with February 2026 seeing significant new releases and growing adoption.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
