      "Based on the search results, I found information about **Inspector** on Product Hunt. Here are the key details:\n\n## Inspector - AI Visual Editing Tool\n\n**Launch Date:** February 8, 2026 (Beijing time)\n\n**Tagline:** \"Figma for Claude Code\"\n\n**Description:**\nInspector is a visual editing tool that connects with your favorite AI assistants (such as Claude Code, Codex, Cursor). You simply click on an element in the user interface, make visual adjustments, and Inspector automatically writes these changes into your codebase. Say goodbye to design handoffs - push directly to your code repository.\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Visual editing interface for AI-powered code modifications\n- Integrates with popular AI coding assistants (Claude Code, Codex, Cursor)\n- Click-to-edit functionality on UI elements\n- Automatic code generation from visual changes\n- Direct push to code repositories\n- Eliminates traditional design-to-development handoff process\n\n**Performance:**\n- Upvotes: 462\n- Featured: Yes (was selected as a featured product)\n\n**Keywords:** Visual editor, AI assistant, Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, UI elements, code changes, design delivery, code repository\n\nInspector appears to bridge the gap between visual design and code implementation, allowing designers and developers to make visual changes that automatically translate into code changes through AI assistance."
