**\n\n### **1. Real Task Execution Capabilities**\n- Transforms from \"dialogue\" to \"execution\" - not just chatting, but actually doing work\n- Executes complex tasks automatically after user authorization\n- Cross-application task execution capabilities\n- No complex command line needed - features a graphical interface similar to Claude Cowork\n\n### **2. Comprehensive Task Coverage (16 Built-in Skills)**\n- **Document Processing**: Word, Excel, PowerPoint, PDF\n- **Data Analysis & Report Generation**\n- **Web Search & Research Collection**\n- **Canvas Poster Design & Frontend UI Prototyping**\n- **Video Generation** (based on Remotion)\n- **Web Automation** (Playwright-driven)\n- **Email Management & Auto-reply**\n- **Scheduled Tasks & Long-term Memory**\n\n### **3. Cross-device Remote Interaction**\n- Mobile and PC integration\n- Can send commands through DingTalk (钉钉), Feishu (飞书), and other IM platforms\n- Control your home computer from anywhere with your phone\n\n### **4. Local-First Security Strategy**\n- **Sandbox Security**: Runs in specified folders within a sandbox environment by default\n- **Local Data Processing**: Data stays local, not sent to the cloud\n- **Dual Engine Support**: Pre-configured with mainstream LLM APIs, also supports local open-source models via Ollama (like DeepSeek)\n\n### **5. Timing & Memory**\n- **Scheduled Tasks**: Set recurring tasks like \"collect tech news every day at 9 AM\"\n- **Long Context Memory**: Learns your preferences over time for personalized experiences\n\n---\n\n## **Application Scenarios**\n\n- **Daily Office Work**: Document processing, data analysis, PPT generation\n- **Information Gathering**: Auto-collect industry news, organize email summaries, web research\n- **Content Creation**: Canvas poster design, video generation, frontend UI prototyping\n- **Remote Work**: Command your home computer from your phone via DingTalk/Feishu\n- **Automation Workflows**: Web automation, scheduled task execution, email auto-reply\n- **Personal Assistant**: Personalized service based on long-term memory learning\n\n---\n\n## **Technical Architecture**\n\n- **Built with**: Electron + React + TypeScript\n- **Clear architecture design** for easy community contribution\n- **Platforms Supported**: macOS (Intel + Apple Silicon) and Windows\n- **Storage**: Local SQLite database (all chat records and configs stored locally)\n- **IM Integration**: DingTalk Stream, Feishu SDK\n\n---\n\n## **How It Works**\n\n1. **One-click Installation**: Download and use, no complex configuration needed\n2. **Natural Language Interaction**: Give commands through the graphical interface\n3. **Authorization**: Authorize complex workflow execution\n4. **Result Delivery**: Agent automatically executes and delivers results\n5. **Remote Use**: Bridge to DingTalk, Feishu, etc. for mobile control\n\n---\n\n## **Safety & Security**\n\n**Q: Will LobsterAI accidentally delete my computer files?**\nA: No. It uses a sandbox mechanism, running in designated folders by default to prevent accidental damage to system files.\n\n**Q: Is my data safe?**\nA: Yes. LobsterAI adopts a \"local-first\" strategy:\n- All chat records and config data stored in local SQLite database\n- Data processed locally, eliminating cloud leak risks\n- Sensitive operations can run in isolated Linux virtual machines\n\n---\n\n## **Pricing & Availability**\n\n- Currently in beta testing stage\n- **Open-sourced on February 19, 2026** \n- Requires application through the official website\n- **Completely free and open-source** (MIT license)\n\n---\n\n## **Why LobsterAI is Important**\n\nLobsterAI represents an important innovation in China's Agent赛道 (Agent track). It combines:\n- The technical depth of OpenClaw\n- The usability of Claude Cowork\n- A \"local-first\" strategy addressing user security concerns about AI automation\n\nIt provides both personal and enterprise users with a truly viable full-scenario AI assistant solution, making powerful AI agent technology accessible to ordinary users, not just developers.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
